==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wahoo
<hw>Wa*hoo"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Any of various
American trees or shrubs;</def> <specif>specif.:</specif> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>A certain shrub (<spn>Evonymus atropurpureus</spn>) having purple
capsules which in dehiscence expose the scarlet-ariled seeds; -- called
also <altname>burning bush</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Cascara
buckthorn.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>Basswood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wahoo</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wahoo
<hw>Wa*hoo"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A dark blue scombroid food fish
(<spn>Acanthocibium solandri</spn> <it>or</it> <spn>Acanthocibium
petus</spn>) of Florida and the West Indies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waid</ent>⟦br⟧
